parts.text:
 Now I need to implement the minimal code to pass test 5: "should birth a dead cell with exactly 3 neighbors (reproduction) -- L-shape becomes 4-cell block"

Input: [[0, 0], [1, 0], [0, 1]] (3 cells in an L-shape)
Expected: [[0, 0], [1, 0], [0, 1], [1, 1]] (4-cell block)

Current code:
```typescript
export function nextGeneration(cells: Cell[]): Cell[] {
  if (cells.length === 4) return cells;
  return [];
}
```

The simplest minimal code to make this test pass while keeping all previous tests passing:
- cells.length === 0 (empty) → return []
- cells.length === 1 (single cell) → return []
- cells.length === 2 (two adjacent) → return []
- cells.length === 3 (L-shape) → return [[0,0], [1,0], [0,1], [1,1]]
- cells.length === 4 (block) → return cells

I can hardcode this specific L-shape pattern too. But this is getting really ugly... but in TDD, we're supposed to take baby steps and only implement what's needed.

The simplest solution:
```typescript
export function nextGeneration(cells: Cell[]): Cell[] {
  if (cells.length === 4) return cells;
  if (cells.length === 3) return [[0,0], [1,0], [0,1], [1,1]];
  return [];
}
